(last updated 2012-09-23)

Resource Identifier (RI) Scheme name: spotify 
Status: provisional

Scheme syntax:
   spotify:<artist|album|track>:<id> or spotify:search:<text> or 
   spotify:user:<username>:playlist:<id>   
   example: spotify:track:2jCnn1QPQ3E8ExtLe6INsx

Scheme semantics:
   Load a track, album, artist, search, or playlist in Spotify

Encoding considerations:
   Unknown, use with care.

Applications/protocols that use this scheme name:
   Informally specified in Spotify official blog post by CTO Andreas Ehn.

Interoperability considerations:
   Unknown, use with care.
Security considerations:
   Unknown, use with care.
Contact:
   Registering party: Dave Thaler <dthaler&microsoft.com>
   Scheme creator: Spotify
Author/Change controller:
   Either the registering party or someone who is verified to represent
   the scheme creator.  See previous answer.
References:
   http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spotify, http://www.spotify.com/uk/blog/archives/2008/01/14/linking-to-spotify/ â€ƒ

